      "correct": "Bowlby identified the critical period for forming primary attachment as roughly from birth to about 3 years of age. During this time, infants have an innate biological drive to form attachment bonds with caregivers.",
      "incorrect": {
        "Birth to 6 months": "This timeframe is too short. While attachment begins forming early, Bowlby's critical period extends much longer to allow for the full development of secure attachment bonds.",
        "3 to 7 years": "This is incorrect as the critical period begins at birth, not at 3 years. By age 3, the primary attachment should already be established.",
