        "Accommodation": "Accommodation would occur if the child modified her schema after learning the cow is different from dogs. For example, creating a new 'cow' category or adjusting her understanding of what makes an animal a dog versus other farm animals.",
        "Conservation": "Conservation is the understanding that basic properties stay the same despite changes in appearance (e.g., liquid in different shaped containers). This concept is unrelated to categorizing animals.",
        "Egocentrism": "Egocentrism is difficulty viewing the world from another's perspective, characteristic of the preoperational stage. It doesn't relate to how children categorize new objects."
      }
    }
